NEW YORK (AP) — Thieves posing as New York City tourists drove up to an 87-year-old man and swiped his necklace, swapping it out with one made of fake gold, police said Thursday.The snatch-and-switch happened June 16 near Cunningham Park in Queens. The thieves claimed to be travelers from Dubai and engaged the man in conversation to draw him closer to their vehicle, police said.Surveillance video made public Thursday showed the man standing close to the vehicle and the driver reaching for the man’s necklace, unclasping it and at one point removing a hat from the man’s head.The thieves then fled in the vehicle, a white Jeep Grand Cherokee with a covered rear plate, police said.No arrests have been made. Police say they’re investigating the theft as a grand larceny, indicating that the stolen necklace was worth more than $1,000.